olive oil
1 packet gnocchi
1 tin chopped tomatoes
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
pinch chilli flakes
½ tbs brown sugar
20 g butter
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 pear
1 cucumber
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
½ bottle balsamic glaze
1 packet diced bacon

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• In a baking dish, add gnocchi and olive oil (2 1/2 tbs for 2 people / 1/3 cup for 4 people). Season, toss to coat and bake until crispy, 10-14 minutes.
• In the last 5 minutes of cook time, remove baking dish from oven and add diced bacon. Bake until golden and crisp.

• When the gnocchi is cooked, add crushed & sieved tomatoes, garlic & herb seasoning, vegetable stock powder, a pinch of chilli flakes (if using), the brown sugar and butter to the baking dish. Season and stir to combine.
• Sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese and bake until golden, 8-10 minutes.

• While the gnocchi is baking, thinly slice pear and cucumber.
• In a medium bowl, add pear, cucumber, spinach & rocket mix and balsamic & olive oil dressing. Season and toss to coat.

• Divide garlic, herb and bacon gnocchi traybake between bowls.
• Serve with pear salad. Enjoy!